		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>Wondrous Item - Legendary (Requires Attunement by a Cleric or Paladin)</em></p><p><strong>Buff</strong> - This talisman is a mighty symbol of goodness. A Fiend or an Undead that touches the talisman takes 8d6 Radiant damage and takes the damage again each time it ends its turn holding or carrying the talisman.</p><p><strong>Attack</strong> - <em><strong>Holy Symbol.</strong></em> You can use the talisman as a Holy Symbol. You gain a +2 bonus to spell attack rolls while you wear or hold it.</p><p><strong>Activation</strong> - 7 Charges (Destroys Item at 0 Charges) <strong>Pure Rebuke.</strong> While wearing or holding the talisman, you can expend 1 charge to target one creature you can see on the ground within 120 feet. A flaming fissure opens under the target, which makes a [[/save DEX 20]]{DC 20 Dexterity saving throw} (Fiends and Undead have Disadvantage). On a failed save, the target falls into the fissure and is destroyed, leaving no remains. On a successful save, the target remains outside the fissure but takes 4d6 Psychic damage. The fissure closes immediately after the effect, and when you expend the last charge the talisman disperses into motes of golden light and is destroyed.</p>",
			"chat": ""
		},
